title: Grateful Dead Live at Capital Centre on 1978-11-23
lineage: SBD> MR> R> C> D> CD> EAC> SHN
description: Mississippi Half Step-> Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, Stagger Lee, Looks Like Rain, Tennessee Jed, Passenger, Brown Eyed Women, The Music Never Stopped Samson & Delilah, Friend Of The Devil, Dancin' In The Streets-> Terrapin Station-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Shakedown Street-> Playin' In The Band-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Beautiful Thanks to someone out there for this soundboard.  This must have been a real treat to see live.
This is a great show, one of the best of '78 The problem is the tape is of iffy quality and the editing jumps between a board and an iffy audience - proceed caveat emptor. Show a 5, tape a 3.

Didn;t realize it them This was a good show song selection wise.  The Mix of SBD and AUD is a flaw.  

This was the first show I took my wife to be to.  Any seat in this place is far away.

This offering of the show with a little love patience and an equalizer will help it out.

I agree 3 star recording 5 star show

Thinking about it.  Wherer did the board part come from and why isn't there more or at least a whole of the Aud used for the 2nd set since it's much better than the Aud used for the 1st.

Also did I mention what a pain stream show are to reassemble
got show? how do i d/l this show please me first

Great Show Show 5! Soundboard 2.5. This was an awesome show. My best Dead show by far. Jerry was feeling under the weather but it didn't show. If I wasn't a devout Deadhead before the show, I was definitely hooked on the way out the door. I remember I was wearing engineers overalls with a Stagger Lee (cover art from the Shakedown Street album) on the front pocket. I remember being surrounded by some traveling Deadheads and I could feel the love. It was a special night. A moment captured in time.
many worlds we've known wish i could know now what i knew then! thanks
